This statement by the President of the United States, issued on February 7, 2011, congratulates the people of Southern Sudan on their successful referendum for independence. The United States intends to formally recognize Southern Sudan as a sovereign, independent state in July 2011. The President emphasizes the need for the Comprehensive Peace Agreement to be fully implemented and outstanding disputes to be resolved peacefully. Additionally, he calls for an end to attacks on civilians in Darfur and a definitive end to that conflict. The United States pledges to continue supporting the aspirations of all Sudanese and will work with both Sudan and Southern Sudan to ensure a smooth and peaceful transition to independence. The statement also mentions the possibility of examining Sudan's designation as a State Sponsor of Terrorism for those who meet their obligations. The President assures that the United States will be a steady partner and friend in the journey towards a future of dignity and peace.